, "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Socialism ", "last_comment_created": 1780198084996, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 34, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 0, "created": 1780081789000, "id": "2060438480132423684", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1473477751323701250/lTIrRTRL_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Nathan J Robinson", "username": "NathanJRobinson"}, "content": "Fascism is about hate and destruction, socialism is about building a better world in which we can all flourish.", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 3605}, "images": [{"width": 1600, "heightRatio": 70, "url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HJmCS4vXUAE1kcq.jpg", "height": 1129}], "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 13, "created": 1780173124000, "id": "2060821568272416980", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1750334337076121600/aRhciHRe_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Chris Freiman", "username": "cafreiman"}, "content": "Fictional socialism is about building a better world in which we can all flourish; real-world socialism is this:", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 499}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsiTEVxB", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 16, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8650351, "raw_content": "For those who think any harsh criticism of Trump makes you a traitor or means you're not MAGA, you definitely weren't paying attention in his early days.\n\n\n**Examples from TD 2016-2020 era:**\n\n\n\"Trump needs better advisors\" was always a huge one on The_Donald. And it's not like it's false. Plenty of his picks ended up getting fired by him. That pattern still shows up today with Pam Bondi and others.\n\nAfter 2017 Las Vegas shooting, Trump directed the DOJ/ATF to ban bump stocks, which defied NRA-aligned hardcore 2A expectations. People on T_D were pretty pissed and vocal about it.\n\nOperation Warp Speed and pushing the COVID vaccines: Large portion of us and the base openly disagreed, criticized him heavily, and many refused to take it.\n\nContinued funding for Ukraine (and other foreign entanglements) drew flak from us who wanted stricter America First policies.\n\n\n**Now today it's things like:**\n\n \n-Foreign policy and \"no new wars\" promises\n-Tariffs and economic ripple effects\n-H-1B and H-2 visas\n-Etc.\n\nAnd that's fine. It's actually good. Anytime Trump has gone off course, the base voiced their reasons and tried to pull him back toward what was promised. That doesn't mean they hate Trump, are bots, or shills. It just means they have a mind of their own and want the president to deliver what's best for the country. \n\nWe have a lot of common interests and Its fine to not agree on everything. Impossible actually.", "author": "FBIAREFAGGOTS", "created": 1780209868648, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Zennblack", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Criticism of Trump Here Isn't New and It Doesn't Make You A Bad Supporter", "last_comment_created": 1780221506902, "content": "<p>For those who think any harsh criticism of Trump makes you a traitor or means you're not MAGA, you definitely weren't paying attention in his early days.</p>\n<p><strong>Examples from TD 2016-2020 era:</strong></p>\n<p>&quot;Trump needs better advisors&quot; was always a huge one on The_Donald. And it's not like it's false. Plenty of his picks ended up getting fired by him. That pattern still shows up today with Pam Bondi and others.</p>\n<p>After 2017 Las Vegas shooting, Trump directed the DOJ/ATF to ban bump stocks, which defied NRA-aligned hardcore 2A expectations. People on T_D were pretty pissed and vocal about it.</p>\n<p>Operation Warp Speed and pushing the COVID vaccines: Large portion of us and the base openly disagreed, criticized him heavily, and many refused to take it.</p>\n<p>Continued funding for Ukraine (and other foreign entanglements) drew flak from us who wanted stricter America First policies.</p>\n<p><strong>Now today it's things like:</strong></p>\n<p>-Foreign policy and &quot;no new wars&quot; promises\n-Tariffs and economic ripple effects\n-H-1B and H-2 visas\n-Etc.</p>\n<p>And that's fine. It's actually good. Anytime Trump has gone off course, the base voiced their reasons and tried to pull him back toward what was promised. That doesn't mean they hate Trump, are bots, or shills. It just means they have a mind of their own and want the president to deliver what's best for the country.</p>\n<p>We have a lot of common interests and Its fine to not agree on everything. Impossible actually.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 3, "score_up": 16, "is_edited": true, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsdwm0MZ", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 294, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "jeb", "id": 8649067, "raw_content": "", "author": "MemeWarsVet", "created": 1780152923666, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDon